==English==

===Etymology===
English (more accurately, American English, perfected in Washington, DC): Abbreviation for random

===Noun===

'''rando'''

# A person who is unknown, unexpected, unanticipated, or generally unbeknownst to the group he/she joins. 
#: ''The jogging club anxiously awaited the arrival of a '''rando''', Carol, who quickly became their star member and no longer warranted that label.''